# Changelog

## v1.0.8

Post-publication update of Elementti.

### Changed

* Simplified demo loading to one **Load demo data** option.
* Demo data are fixed and repeatable by default.
* Demo CSV files include metadata rows and detectable pixel-size information.
* Improved demo temporary-folder handling and cleanup.
* Updated icon and welcome-image resource names to `icoElementti_1_0_8.ico` and `pngElementti_1_0_8.png`.
* Improved Windows app icon handling for EXE/taskbar use.
* Removed unused old preview code.

### Fixed

* Added safer export filenames to prevent accidental overwriting.

## v1.0.7

* Made line-length labels draw above the red arrow.
* Improved automatic guide-bar endpoint rounding, for example `1.78378` becomes `1.8`.
* Made line-profile legends draw above curves for better readability.

## v1.0.6

* Reduced guide-bar and y-axis label clutter near clipped endpoint labels.
* Added line-profile legend placement option: **Inside plot** or **Outside right**.

## v1.0.5

* Added clearer display min/max guide-bar labels such as `≥21` and `≤0`.
* Line-profile x-axis now uses physical distance when pixel size is available.
* Added dual y-axes for mixed element and ratio profiles.
* Added optional manual y-axis limits for line profiles.

## v1.0.4

* Simplified the formula-map interface.
* Moved formula examples into **Read instructions**.
* Changed line-profile end marker to an arrow to show direction.

## v1.0.3

* Added custom formula maps.
* Supports expressions such as `X + Y / Z`, `(X + Y) / Z`, `X / (Y + Z)`, `sqrt(X)`, and `log10(X)`.
* Input names with spaces or symbols can be written as `[Exact input name]` or `{Exact input name}`.
* Added safe formula parsing and validation.

## v1.0.2

* Added unit-aware pixel-size handling.
* Pixel size can be detected or entered in `nm`, `um/µm`, `mm`, `cm`, or `m`.
* Values are converted internally to `µm/pixel`.

## v1.0.1

* Original baseline version.
* Supports CSV map loading, map selection, simple ratios, display settings, masks, scale bars, line profiles, and export.

## Notes

* The SoftwareX-published version is **v1.0.0**.
* The current updated post-publication version is **v1.0.8**.
* Always check detected pixel size before final export.
* Display min/max changes the color scale; it does not remove data.
* Values above display max use the top color, and values below display min use the bottom color.
